# Feature: Custom Pages with Homepage Toggle

## Goal

Enable admins to set any custom page as the homepage (landing-slug) directly from the custom pages UI, via a toggle or selection control. This should be secure, intuitive, and update the landing page in real time for all users.

## Steps

1. Backend: Expose/update an endpoint to set the landing-slug (homepage) to a given custom page slug. Ensure only admins can perform this action.
2. Frontend: Add a toggle or selection control in the custom pages admin UI to set/unset a page as the homepage.
3. Frontend: Visually indicate which page is currently the homepage.
4. Backend: Broadcast landing page changes via WebSocket to all connected clients for real-time update.
5. Frontend: Listen for landing page change events and update UI accordingly.
6. Update documentation and specs as needed.
7. Add/extend tests for backend and frontend to cover this feature.

